snippet.title: Domestic Violence NSW
snippet.description:
Domestic Violence NSW is the peak representative body for a range of specialist domestic and family violence services in New South Wales.

Our vision is of a world where women, families and communities live free from violence, have equal rights and opportunities and the freedom to reach their potential.

Operating from a feminist, social justice perspective, we work with government and the sector to improve policy, legislative and program responses to domestic and family violence, (DFV) and to eliminate DFV through advocacy, partnerships and the promotion of good practice.
